  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate-resilient water management approaches: Application towards Climate Action and 2030 Development Agenda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall objective of the project is to compile CRIDA case study applications to improve national risk management strategies and to lower the impact of water-related hazards on vulnerable communities through the implementation of the CRIDA methodology by partner organizations in pilot regions of Africa, Asia and Latin America. Furthermore, the project aims to strengthen the communication and outreach of successful applications of bottom-up approaches to adaptation and water management, as well as relevant information for decision making through a global conference on climate-resilient water management approaches and policy document.</narrative>
  </description>
